SAMPLE PROGRAMS FOR EVERY LANGUAGE
1.	Write a program to print “Hello world!”.
2.	Write a program to print “hello world” each word on a different line.
3.	Write a program to calculate the sum, difference, product, and quotient of two initialised numbers. 
4.	Write a program to take two numbers as input and print their sum, difference, product, and quotient. 
5.	Write a program to calculate the average of two numbers. 
6.	Write a program to calculate the rectangle, triangle, circle, and square area. 
7.	Write a program to calculate the volume of a cube, cuboid, cone, sphere, and cylinder. 
8.	Write a program to accept values of different data types and display them. 
9.	Write a program to find the ASCII value of a character.
10.	Write a program to convert numbers into characters. 
11.	Write a program to calculate simple interest and compound interest.
12.	Write a program to swap two numbers using the third variable. 
13.	 Write a program to swap two numbers without using the third variable. 
14.	 Write a program to calculate gross salary & net salary.
            DA = 70% of basic salary
            HRA = 20% of basic salary
            PF = 5% of basic salary
            GS = b + D + H
            NS = GS – PF
15.	Write a program to read the 5 subject marks of a student and calculate the total and average marks of the student. 
16.	Write a program to convert the temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit and vice-versa. 
17.	A cricket team has the following table of batting figures for a series of test matches. 
    Player’s name	        Runs	    Innings	      Times not out
    Sachin	              8430	    230	          18
    Saurav	              4200	    130	          8
    Rahul	                3350	    105	          11
    Write a program to read the figures set out in the above form to calculate the batting average and to print out the complete table including the average.
18.	Write a program to demonstrate the use of short-hand arithmetic operators. 
19.	Write a program to demonstrate the use of all relational operators.
20.	Write a program to demonstrate the use of all logical operators. 
21.	Write a program to demonstrate the use of all bitwise operators. 
22.	Write a program to demonstrate the use of increment/decrement operators. 
23.	 Write a program to calculate the years, months, weeks, and days with a number taken as input. 
24.	Write a program to check whether a given number is even or odd. 
25.	Write a program to check whether a candidate is eligible to vote or not. 
26.	Write a program to find the largest of two numbers. 
27.	Write a program to check whether a given year is a leap year. 
28.	 Write a program to check whether a number is positive, negative or zero. 
29.	Write a program to check the class of a student. 
              <35 = fail
              35 – 49 = just pass
              50 – 59 = 2nd class
              60 – 84 = 1st class
              85 – 100 = distinction 
30.	Write a program to check whether two numbers are equal using conditional statements. 
31.	Write a program to find the largest of three numbers.
32.	Write a program to check the eligibility of a candidate for a professional course. 
33.	Write a program to take input from three sides of a triangle and check whether the triangle is isosceles, scalene or equilateral. 
34.	 Write a program to check whether a given character is a number, alphabet or special character. 
35.	Write a number that gives the number in words. 
              For eg – If the input is 23  The output must be “Twenty-three”
36.	Write a program to check whether a character entered is a vowel or a consonant.
37.	Write a program to print the numbers from (1,2,3,4………100) and (100,99,98,97,…..1).
38.	Write a program to print the even and odd numbers in the range 1-100. 
39.	Write a program to print the even numbers in the given range. 
40.	Write a program to calculate the sum of n numbers.
41.	Write a program to reverse a given number.
42.	Write a program to calculate the sum of digits of a given number.
43.	Write a program to generate the multiplication table of a number. 
44.	Write a program to print the following pattern.
    1
    22
    333
    4444
    55555
45.	Write a program to find the factorial of a number.
46.	Write a program to print the alphabet triangle. 
47.	Write a program to display the Fibonacci series.
48.	Write a program to print the Fibonacci triangle.
49.	Write a program to calculate the GCD and LCM of two numbers. 
50.	Write a program to calculate the power of a number without using built-in functions.
51.	Write a program to display prime numbers in a given range. 
52.	Write a program to check whether the given number is an Armstrong number. 
53.	Write a program to check whether the given number is an Adam number. 
54.	Write a program to display the factors of a given number.
55.	Write a program to convert decimal numbers to binary. 
56.	Write a program to enter a number and print the month (switch statement)
57.	Write a program to calculate the roots of a quadratic equation. 
58.	Write a program to check whether a number is a palindrome.
59.	Write a program to find the minimum and maximum value from a set of real values.
60.	Write a program to demonstrate the bubble sort. 
61.	Write a program to demonstrate binary search. 
62.	Write a program to demonstrate the multiplication of 2 matrices. 
63.	 Write a program to demonstrate the concatenation of two strings. 
64.	Write a program to demonstrate the functions of strings. 
